    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-06T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-06T20:00:00-05:00" n="753"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-06T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1916, 8 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3007. Your 3841 of February 23. Inform Foreign Office that porcelain guides for
                        <persName>Mitchell</persName>-Bissell Company requested on behalf of State
                    Department should be given immediate decision. Both in this <pb facs="0855"
                        n="569" xml:id="pg_569"/> and cyanide application remind Foreign Office that
                    Secretary of Commerce was assured by English Ambassador that applications for
                    goods necessary for American industries would be granted. Delay is causing
                    inestimable harm.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
